{
  "page": "Kingswood Brotherhood",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background: #DEDEE2; text-align:center;\">Kingswood Brotherhood</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Type</th><td>\nOutlaw group</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Seat</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Kingswood\" title=\"Kingswood\">Kingswood</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Founder</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Simon_Toyne\" title=\"Simon Toyne\">Simon Toyne</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Disbanded</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/281_AC\" title=\"281 AC\">281&#160;AC</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The <b>Kingswood Brotherhood</b> was an infamous <a href=\"/index.php/Outlaw\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Outlaw\">outlaw</a> organization which operated out of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingswood\" title=\"Kingswood\">kingswood</a> during the reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aerys_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerys II Targaryen\">Aerys II Targaryen</a>. The bandits were led by <a href=\"/index.php/Simon_Toyne\" title=\"Simon Toyne\">Simon Toyne</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> and they were eventually suppressed by a royal force commanded by Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Arthur_Dayne\" title=\"Arthur Dayne\">Arthur Dayne</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafdorne:_the_andals_arrive.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafdorne:_the_andals_arrive.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Songs\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Songs</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Known_members_of_the_Brotherhood\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Known members of the Brotherhood</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Kingswood_Brotherhood&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:SirHeartsalot_The_Smiling_Knight.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/ab/SirHeartsalot_The_Smiling_Knight.jpg/300px-SirHeartsalot_The_Smiling_Knight.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"315\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/ab/SirHeartsalot_The_Smiling_Knight.jpg/450px-SirHeartsalot_The_Smiling_Knight.jpg 1.5x, /images/a/ab/SirHeartsalot_The_Smiling_Knight.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:SirHeartsalot_The_Smiling_Knight.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The <a href=\"/index.php/Smiling_Knight\" title=\"Smiling Knight\">Smiling Knight</a>, by Sir-Heartsalot ©</div></div></div>\n<p>Operating out of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingswood\" title=\"Kingswood\">kingswood</a>, the Brotherhood gained recognition by robbing and kidnapping nobles and, with <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">smallfolk</a> helping them,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> they evaded attempts to capture them for years.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafarthur_dayne.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafarthur_dayne.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> The outlaws hid in the forests and used their numbers to surprise smaller parties.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasosepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasosepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Victor_Tyrell\" title=\"Victor Tyrell\">Victor Tyrell</a>, cousin of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Mace_Tyrell\" title=\"Mace Tyrell\">Mace Tyrell</a>, was slain by the <a href=\"/index.php/Smiling_Knight\" title=\"Smiling Knight\">Smiling Knight</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Gerold_Hightower\" title=\"Gerold Hightower\">Gerold Hightower</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Commander_of_the_Kingsguard\" title=\"Lord Commander of the Kingsguard\">Lord Commander of the Kingsguard</a>, was shot through the hand by <a href=\"/index.php/Ulmer_of_the_Kingswood\" title=\"Ulmer of the Kingswood\">Ulmer of the Kingswood</a> when the outlaws attacked Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Elia_Martell\" title=\"Elia Martell\">Elia Martell</a>'s escort through the woods, and Ulmer went on to steal a kiss and some jewels from the <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dornish</a> princess.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Fletcher_Dick\" title=\"Fletcher Dick\">Fletcher Dick</a>, the outlaw who taught Ulmer, is considered among the greatest archers to have ever lived.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_the_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_the_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The outlaws eventually became such a nuisance that King <a href=\"/index.php/Aerys_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerys II Targaryen\">Aerys II Targaryen</a> sent a detachment of soldiers led by Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Arthur_Dayne\" title=\"Arthur Dayne\">Arthur Dayne</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a> to destroy them. Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Sumner_Crakehall\" title=\"Sumner Crakehall\">Sumner Crakehall</a> and his two squires, <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Merrett_Frey\" title=\"Merrett Frey\">Merrett Frey</a>, were also part of the retinue. Merrett contracted the <a href=\"/index.php/Pox\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pox\">pox</a> from a camp follower, and he was also captured by <a href=\"/index.php/Wenda_the_White_Fawn\" title=\"Wenda the White Fawn\">Wenda the White Fawn</a>; the bandit woman branded her sigil on Merrett's arse before ransoming him back to Lord Crakehall.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> When he next faced the Brotherhood in combat, Merrett was heavily wounded by a mace strike on his helm. Though he survived the battle, the squire was never able to fight again.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasosepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasosepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Arthur gained the confidence of the smallfolk, who had believed that the only ones protecting their rights was the Brotherhood. The <a href=\"/index.php/Sword_of_the_Morning\" title=\"Sword of the Morning\">Sword of the Morning</a> petitioned King Aerys for better rights for the smallfolk, and he made sure the royal forces paid for any items they took from the peasantry. Arthur's actions swung the allegiance of the smallfolk to the royal forces, who could now hunt the Brotherhood, as the outlaws could no longer walk around with impunity in the forest.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Barristan_Selmy\" title=\"Barristan Selmy\">Barristan Selmy</a> of the Kingsguard rescued Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Jeyne_Swann\" title=\"Jeyne Swann\">Jeyne Swann</a> and her <a href=\"/index.php/Septa\" title=\"Septa\">septa</a> from the Kingswood Brotherhood, defeating the Smiling Knight and slaying the outlaws' leader, Simon Toyne.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> Young Jaime Lannister saved Lord Crakehall's life by fending off <a href=\"/index.php/Big_Belly_Ben\" title=\"Big Belly Ben\">Big Belly Ben</a>, but the outlaw was able to escape the confrontation.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> Jaime also crossed swords with the mad Smiling Knight, with the fearsome bandit then being slain by Arthur with his legendary longsword, <a href=\"/index.php/Dawn\" title=\"Dawn\">Dawn</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> Arthur knighted Jaime for his valor on the battlefield,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> with Arthur touching the fifteen-year-old's shoulders with Dawn after he stood vigil in a <a href=\"/index.php/Sept\" title=\"Sept\">sept</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In the aftermath of the Brotherhood's defeat, King Aerys chose Jaime to replace the late Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Harlan_Grandison\" title=\"Harlan Grandison\">Harlan Grandison</a> in the Kingsguard;<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> Jaime became the youngest ever member of the White Swords.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok55.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok55.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Ulmer_of_the_Kingswood\" title=\"Ulmer of the Kingswood\">Ulmer of the Kingswood</a> was captured and allowed to join the <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafulmer.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafulmer.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup> The fates of the other outlaws are unknown, though they are presumably dead.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Kingswood_Brotherhood&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Kingswood_Brotherhood&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Ser_Arthur_Dayne_by_henning.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/65/Ser_Arthur_Dayne_by_henning.jpg/300px-Ser_Arthur_Dayne_by_henning.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"250\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/65/Ser_Arthur_Dayne_by_henning.jpg/450px-Ser_Arthur_Dayne_by_henning.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/65/Ser_Arthur_Dayne_by_henning.jpg/600px-Ser_Arthur_Dayne_by_henning.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Ser_Arthur_Dayne_by_henning.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Arthur_Dayne\" title=\"Arthur Dayne\">Arthur Dayne</a>, by Henning Ludvigsen © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Tom_of_Sevenstreams\" title=\"Tom of Sevenstreams\">Tom of Sevenstreams</a>, a member of the outlaw <a href=\"/index.php/Brotherhood_without_banners\" title=\"Brotherhood without banners\">brotherhood without banners</a>, sings a song about the Kingswood Brotherhood while traveling in the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Ulmer_of_the_Kingswood\" title=\"Ulmer of the Kingswood\">Ulmer of the Kingswood</a> frequently tells tales of his time with the Brotherhood to his fellow members of the <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Merrett_Frey\" title=\"Merrett Frey\">Merrett Frey</a> recalls fighting the Kingswood Brotherhood while traveling to <a href=\"/index.php/Oldstones\" title=\"Oldstones\">Oldstones</a> to ransom <a href=\"/index.php/Petyr_Frey\" title=\"Petyr Frey\">Petyr Frey</a> from the brotherhood without banners, but both Freys are hanged by the outlaws now led by <a href=\"/index.php/Lady_Stoneheart\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lady Stoneheart\">Lady Stoneheart</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasosepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasosepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Kingswood_Brotherhood&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a>,  <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Commander_of_the_Kingsguard\" title=\"Lord Commander of the Kingsguard\">Lord Commander of the Kingsguard</a>, speaks about Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Arthur_Dayne\" title=\"Arthur Dayne\">Arthur Dayne</a>'s methods of defeating the Kingswood Brotherhood while meeting with Merrett's family at <a href=\"/index.php/Darry\" title=\"Darry\">Darry</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Songs\">Songs</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Kingswood_Brotherhood&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Songs\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:252px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Simon_Toyne_TheMico.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/37/Simon_Toyne_TheMico.jpg/250px-Simon_Toyne_TheMico.jpg\" width=\"250\" height=\"354\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/37/Simon_Toyne_TheMico.jpg/375px-Simon_Toyne_TheMico.jpg 1.5x, /images/3/37/Simon_Toyne_TheMico.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Simon_Toyne_TheMico.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Simon_Toyne\" title=\"Simon Toyne\">Simon Toyne</a>, by The Mico ©</div></div></div>\n<p>One song  about the Brotherhood includes the lyrics:\n</p>\n<dl><dd><dl><dd><dl><dd><i>The brothers of the Kingswood,</i></dd>\n<dd><i>they were an outlaw band.</i></dd>\n<dd><i>The forest was their castle,</i></dd>\n<dd><i>but they roamed across the land.</i></dd>\n<dd><i>No man's gold was safe from them,</i></dd>\n<dd><i>nor any maiden's hand.</i></dd>\n<dd><i>Oh, the brothers of the Kingswood,</i></dd>\n<dd><i>that fearsome outlaw band ...</i><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl>\n<p>There is also a silly song about <a href=\"/index.php/Big_Belly_Ben\" title=\"Big Belly Ben\">Big Belly Ben</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/High_Septon\" title=\"High Septon\">High Septon</a>'s <a href=\"/index.php/Goose\" title=\"Goose\">goose</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_16-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Known_members_of_the_Brotherhood\">Known members of the Brotherhood</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Kingswood_Brotherhood&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Known members of the Brotherhood\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Big_Belly_Ben\" title=\"Big Belly Ben\">Big Belly Ben</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Fletcher_Dick\" title=\"Fletcher Dick\">Fletcher Dick</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Oswyn_Longneck_the_Thrice-Hanged\" title=\"Oswyn Longneck the Thrice-Hanged\">Oswyn Longneck the Thrice-Hanged</a></li>\n<li>The <a href=\"/index.php/Smiling_Knight\" title=\"Smiling Knight\">Smiling Knight</a>, slain by Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Arthur_Dayne\" title=\"Arthur Dayne\">Arthur Dayne</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Simon_Toyne\" title=\"Simon Toyne\">Simon Toyne</a>, slain by Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Barristan_Selmy\" title=\"Barristan Selmy\">Barristan Selmy</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Ulmer_of_the_Kingswood\" title=\"Ulmer of the Kingswood\">Ulmer of the Kingswood</a>, ranger of the <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Wenda_the_White_Fawn\" title=\"Wenda the White Fawn\">Wenda the White Fawn</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Kingswood_Brotherhood&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:252px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Ulmer_TheMico.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/bc/Ulmer_TheMico.jpg/250px-Ulmer_TheMico.jpg\" width=\"250\" height=\"354\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/bc/Ulmer_TheMico.jpg/375px-Ulmer_TheMico.jpg 1.5x, /images/b/bc/Ulmer_TheMico.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Ulmer_TheMico.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Ulmer_of_the_Kingswood\" title=\"Ulmer of the Kingswood\">Ulmer of the Kingswood</a>, by The Mico ©</div></div></div>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Ulmer\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ulmer\">Ulmer</a>, stooped and grey-bearded and loose of skin and limb, stepped to the mark and pulled an arrow from the quiver at his waist. In his youth he had been an outlaw, a member of the infamous Kingswood Brotherhood. He claimed he'd once put an arrow through the hand of the <a href=\"/index.php/Gerold_Hightower\" title=\"Gerold Hightower\">White Bull</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a> to steal a kiss from the lips of a <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dornish</a> princess. He had stolen her jewels too, and a chest of <a href=\"/index.php/Currency\" title=\"Currency\">golden dragons</a>, but it was the kiss he liked to boast of in his cups.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Samwell_Tarly\" title=\"Samwell Tarly\">Samwell Tarly</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Brotherhood_without_banners\" title=\"Brotherhood without banners\">Bloody outlaws</a>, always hiding in the bushes. It had been the same in the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingswood\" title=\"Kingswood\">kingswood</a>. you'd think you'd caught five of them, and ten more would spring from nowhere.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasosepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasosepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Merrett_Frey\" title=\"Merrett Frey\">Merrett Frey</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>If you want their help, you need to make them love you. That was how <a href=\"/index.php/Arthur_Dayne\" title=\"Arthur Dayne\">Arthur Dayne</a> did it, when we rode against the Kingswood Brotherhood. He paid the <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">smallfolk</a> for the food we ate, brought their grievances to King <a href=\"/index.php/Aerys_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerys II Targaryen\">Aerys</a>, expanded the grazing lands around their villages, even won them the right to fell a certain number of trees each year and take a few of the king's deer during the autumn. The forest folk had looked to <a href=\"/index.php/Simon_Toyne\" title=\"Simon Toyne\">Toyne</a> to defend them, but Ser Arthur did more for them than the Brotherhood could ever hope to do, and won them to our side. After that, the rest was easy.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Lyle_Crakehall\" title=\"Lyle Crakehall\">Lyle Crakehall</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Kingswood_Brotherhood&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Chapter_42\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Chapter 42\">Chapter 42</a>, Daenerys IV.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Targaryen King